    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine with individual throttle bodies. This example is paired with a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission, delivering power to the rear wheels via a variable M differential lock. Crucial preventative maintenance has been addressed, including a complete VANOS system overhaul and rod bearing replacement to ensure long-term reciprocating assembly health. The chassis has been proactively reinforced at the rear subframe mounting points to mitigate fatigue. Performance is further enhanced by a Bilstein PSS10 coilover suite, providing adjustable damping while maintaining optimal roll center geometry. The vehicle sits on staggered 18-inch Style 67 alloys with fresh Michelin Pilot Sport 4S tires. While the exterior displays minor stone chips consistent with spirited use, the drivetrain and suspension kinematics are dialed for the discerning driver.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 36
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Used car. Good condition. Clean title. Regularly serviced. Reliable engine. Minor cosmetic wear only.",
      "price": 29500.0,
